CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1959, page 8, reads: "For Deserving Family - Las Catena Social Club ushered in the New Year by presenting a basket, filled with groceries, to a deserving family, and then celebrating with their husbands and friends at their annual party. Gloria Talbott is president; Thelma Owens, secretary; Alicia Harrison, treasurer; Westina Slaughter, social chairman, Julie Beatty and Elizabeth Mickens are not shown. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, and six women, some members of the Las Catena Social Club, including Gloria Talbott, Thelma Owens, Alicia Harrison, and Westina Slaughter, gathered for a New Years celebration around sofa in interior with light colored walls, door with blinds, and large window with blinds and geometrically patterned curtains
